OL,3,CHead teachers declare 'trade dispute'
OL,4,Cwith Stormont
OL,6,F"We cannot continue to ask leaders to
OL,7,Fsacrifice their own health and safety
OL,8,Fto compensate for a system that is no
OL,9,Flonger functioning," said Dr Graham
OL,10,FGault, national secretary of NAHT(NI).
OL,12,F"School leaders have been holding back
OL,13,Fwhat feels like fire and flood from
OL,14,Fevery direction to protect them. But
OL,15,Fthe pressures have now become
OL,16,Foverwhelming and insurmountable," said
OL,17,FDr Gault.
OL,26,@nD@AOUtD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G3/9
