OL,3,CHead teachers declare 'trade dispute'
OL,4,Cwith Stormont
OL,6,F"This dispute is not about pay, it is
OL,7,Fabout protecting children's education.
OL,8,FWe are urging parents and communities
OL,9,Fto stand with their school leaders.
OL,10,FThey are exhausted, they are on their
OL,11,Fknees, and they need the support of
OL,12,Fthe public to ensure schools remain
OL,13,Fthe safe, stable, welled places
OL,14,Fchildren rely on every day."
OL,16,FNAHT(NI) said in a press release that
OL,17,Fthe education minister has already
OL,18,Fconfirmed that the Department cannot
OL,19,Fdeliver essential workload relief
OL,20,Fmeasures, acknowledging "extreme
OL,21,Ffinancial constraints".
OL,26,@nD@AOUvD@\O]
